Thai Authorities, on Thursday advised travellers from countries affected by the new coronavirus to self-quarantine for two weeks. The Ministry of Public Health said in a statement that those coming from areas affected by the virus should isolate themselves at their accommodation or home for 14 days and avoid going to congested areas. The ministry, however, recommended if it had become necessary for those in self-quarantine to go outside, they should wear face masks and wash their hands regularly in an effort to contain the spread of the virus. The Department of Disease Control has listed China, Hong Kong, Macau, Taiwan, South Korea, Japan, Singapore, Italy, Iran, France, and Germany as countries that are at risk of the new coronavirus. (dpa/NAN)